UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Technical visit', titre_en = 'Carry out a technical inspection of the vehicle', description_en = 'The user goes to Mali Technic System located in Sogoniko or to its regional representations, specifically to the Registration Section. Once the fees have been paid, the inspector inspects the vehicle on the following aspects: brakes, identification, lighting, tires, steering, geometry, signaling, nuisances and accessories (windshield wipers, fire extinguishers, spare wheels, triangles, medicine box). If there are no defects, the validity of all checked items is confirmed. A sticker is then affixed to the windshield. The operating agent gives the first part (part no. 1) of the certificate to the user and the second part (part no. 2) to the regional transport directorate for classification. If there is a defect, the user is subject to a revisit. He has fifteen days to repair the vehicle and return it if it is a light vehicle (1750 FCFA). For public transport and heavy goods vehicles, it has thirty days (2100 FCFA and 2800 FCFA respectively). The technical inspection is obligatory for all vehicles. The first technical inspection takes place 3 years after the first entry into circulation. The frequency of the inspection is: once a year for personal vehicles, twice a year for transport vehicles and heavy goods vehicles.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on vehicle type' WHERE id = 14;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Thumbnail', titre_en = 'Acquire a car sticker', description_en = 'The user presents himself at the tax counters generally from January 1 to March 31 of the current year, equipped with the registration document for vehicles with old registration (from the date of issue of the registration document for vehicles which are on their first registration). He pays the fees and receives the sticker that he must affix to the windshield, as well as a receipt. When the vignette is paid from October 1, the user must pay the half-fare. After payment deadlines, the user is subject to a 100% penalty.', delai_en = 'January 1 to March 31 (normal period)' WHERE id = 15;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Plate color change', titre_en = 'Change the color of number plates', description_en = 'The file is entered for a plate color change. The vehicle must be present. The user goes to the registration document section. The section agent checks the file and approves it for payment at the cash register. After payment, the file returns to the Section where it is registered and numbered. The section agent completes the provisional document form which he transmits to the Head of Division or the Regional Director for signature. The provisional plate color change document returns to the section to be given to the user. The file goes to the Computer Room for entry, then is validated by the agent responsible for validation and returns to the Computer Room for the registration of the registration document. The file returns to the section which sends it to the secretariat for the establishment of the sending slip to the National Directorate. The file is sent to the National Directorate after having been approved by the Head of Division and signed by the Regional Director. At the National Directorate, we register the file and verify its conformity with the parent file. If it is compliant, the Director or his Deputy signs the document, which is returned to the Regional Transport Directorate. The file remains in the archives of the National Directorate. If the file is not compliant, it is rejected. The user or his agent collects the document from the registration document section of the Regional Transport Directorate and proceeds to withdraw the plates by returning the provisional document. He must remove the old plates.', delai_en = '1 month, extendable once for a period of 15 days' WHERE id = 16;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Conditional release', titre_en = 'Apply for parole', description_en = 'Conditional release is a suspension of the execution of a custodial sentence accompanied by a measure of assistance and control, the granting or maintenance of which is subject to the observation of certain conditions. The matter is governed by the Code of Criminal Procedure. Substantive conditions: Any convicted person may be eligible for parole, if the following conditions are met: having been definitively sentenced to one or more custodial sentences, having given sufficient proof of good behavior, giving serious guarantees of social rehabilitation. Formal conditions: Conditional release is reserved for convicts who have completed three months of their sentence, if this sentence is less than 6 months and half of this sentence otherwise. For convicted offenders who are repeat offenders, the probation period is increased to 6 months if the sentence is less than 3 months and to two thirds of the sentence otherwise. For those sentenced to forced labor for life, the probation period is 15 years. In drug matters, conditional release cannot be granted to any convicted person before the execution of 4/5th of the quantum of the sentence imposed.', delai_en = 'Depending on the duration of the work of the prison commission' WHERE id = 17;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Declaration of loss', titre_en = 'Report lost documents', description_en = 'Any person who has lost their papers is allowed to report them immediately in order to avoid fraud and/or use of them by a third party. How is the declaration made? By written or verbal declaration. Who receives the declaration? The competent authority, in particular the prefect, the police station, the gendarmerie in the Public Highways section or the head of the guard post on the day of the declaration in the handrail register. NB: The declaration of certain documents such as the land title does not result in the delivery to the user of a certificate of loss.', delai_en = 'Immediate' WHERE id = 18;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Application for provisional release', titre_en = 'Request provisional release', description_en = 'Provisional release may be requested in any case by any individual of Malian or foreign nationality when they find themselves under arrest, indicted or accused. Provisional release may be ordered either by the investigating judge, or at the request of the public prosecutor, or ex officio. On the condition that the accused undertakes to appear at all acts of the procedure as soon as he is asked and to keep the investigating magistrate informed of all his movements. The accused or his lawyer may request provisional release at any stage of the procedure. However, when release is not legal, it may be subject to the obligation to pay bail or provide security. These guarantee the representation of the accused, the execution of the judgment, the costs advanced by the civil party, the costs advanced by the public party and fines in particular.', delai_en = '8 days after the request addressed to the judge' WHERE id = 19;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Authorization to purchase weapons and ammunition', titre_en = 'Obtain authorization to purchase weapons and ammunition', description_en = 'The authorization to purchase weapons and ammunition allows its holder to purchase or import a weapon or ammunition for hunting or for their own safety. Carrying each weapon requires a separate authorization. Any interested person who is at least 21 years old can request authorization. In the event of loss or theft, you must make a new request or request a duplicate by providing the same documents as for the initial request.', delai_en = 'Several weeks' WHERE id = 20;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Request to visit a prisoner', titre_en = 'Obtain a communication permit to visit a prisoner', description_en = 'The permit to communicate is an act by which the prosecutor or the investigating judge authorizes a citizen to visit a defendant or an accused person in the Remand Prison. In practice, it is also a technique used to observe those who visit him. In principle, the user sends a verbal request to the Judge (through his secretary) who can request a more in-depth interview at the end of which he issues the permit or not. The permit to communicate is free and is valid for a single visit. However, it may be valid for a period, for the close relatives of the accused.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on the interview with the judge' WHERE id = 21;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of SARL', titre_en = 'Create a Limited Liability Company (SARL) in Mali', description_en = 'To create an SARL in Mali, you must draw up the statutes, deposit the share capital, prepare a registration file at the API Mali Single Window, publish it in a legal notice newspaper, then obtain the certificates and registrations from the API. The process includes the drafting of the statutes, the appointment of managers, the deposit of the minimum share capital, the constitution of the registration file, the publication of a notice of creation in a legal notices newspaper, the submission of the complete file and the tax registration. The fees amount to 6,000 FCFA for SARLs.', delai_en = '72 hours after submission of the complete file' WHERE id = 23;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of a limited company (SA)', titre_en = 'Create a Limited Company (SA) in Mali', description_en = 'To create a Limited Company (SA) in Mali, you must go through the Single Window of the Agency for the Promotion of Investments (API-Mali), by submitting the notarized statutes and the incorporation file. The minimum share capital required is 10 million FCFA, divided into shares with a nominal value of 10,000 FCFA minimum. At least half of the cash capital must be released upon creation. The process includes the drafting of the statutes by a notary, the definition of the share capital and contributions, the designation of managers, the publication of a notice of creation in a legal notice newspaper, the filing of the incorporation file and obtaining the official documents.', delai_en = '72 hours after submission of the complete file' WHERE id = 24;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of a Simplified Joint Stock Company (SAS)', titre_en = 'Create a Simplified Joint Stock Company (SAS) in Mali', description_en = 'To create a Simplified Joint Stock Company (SAS) in Mali, you must follow the procedure supervised by the Agency for the Promotion of Investments in Mali (API-Mali) via its Single Window. Mali, as a member of OHADA, applies the Uniform Act relating to the law of commercial companies and Economic Interest Groups, which allows the creation of an SAS or a SASU (SAS with a single shareholder). The SAS offers great contractual freedom, particularly for the distribution of power between the partners. A major advantage of the SAS is that it does not require minimum capital, which facilitates its creation. The process includes drafting the statutes, depositing the share capital, obtaining supporting documents, submitting the file to the Single Window, registration and registration, and publication of the notice of incorporation.', delai_en = '72 hours after submission of the complete file' WHERE id = 25;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of a Simple Limited Partnership (SCS)', titre_en = 'Create a Simple Limited Partnership (SCS)', description_en = 'Corporate form: Société en Commandite Simple (SCS). Particularity: Distinction between general partners (managers) and limited partners (investors). Capital: No minimum capital required. Duration: Maximum 99 years. Registration: Integrated Management Center (CGI) or RCCM. General partners: Manage the company, merchant status required. Limited Partners: Investors, limited liability. Mandatory notary: Unlike other forms. Mandatory publication: Official Journal of Mali.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the complexity of the file' WHERE id = 26;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Transfer of plot for residential use', titre_en = 'Transfer a plot for residential use', description_en = 'To transfer a plot of land for residential use in Mali, you must draw up a notarized deed of sale and register the transfer at the Lands Office. The process involves documents such as the land title or the Final Concession Order (ACD) of the current owner, as well as a written request from the new buyer, proof of ownership, and payment of the costs corresponding to the transfer. The transfer of ownership must go through a notary and the deed of sale must be registered with the competent tax and domain services of Mali.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the complexity of the file' WHERE id = 27;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Verification of property titles', titre_en = 'Check the authenticity of a property title', description_en = 'To verify a property title in Mali, you must go to the National Directorate of Lands and Cadastre (DNDC) for a request for parcel requisition from the competent state service. You can also consult the municipality''s land registry services, which may be able to provide the cadastral plan and the unique national cadastral identification number (NINACAD). These steps ensure that the seller is the owner and that there is no dispute. Verifying a property title is an essential step in securing a real estate transaction. Only the land title is considered an act of ownership guaranteed by the State. Provisional titles must be converted into definitive land titles to strengthen legal certainty.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the complexity of the file' WHERE id = 31;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Complete real estate transaction', titre_en = 'Secure a complete real estate transaction', description_en = 'For a complete real estate transaction in Mali, several delays are added depending on the stages: Sales agreement: The time between the signing of the agreement and the notarized deed of sale is generally 3 to 4 months. This period allows the conditions precedent to be lifted, such as obtaining credit or verifying the property title. Notary verification: Verification by the notary can take 1 to 5 weeks, depending on availability and the complexity of the file, which includes gathering all the necessary documents. Right of pre-emption: Local authorities often have a right of pre-emption, which can add a delay of 60 days to the procedure. In summary, the total time for securing a complete real estate transaction, from verification to obtaining the title, can therefore be several months.', delai_en = 'Several months (depending on the stages)' WHERE id = 32;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Letter of allocation of the provisional rural concession title', titre_en = 'Obtain a provisional rural concession allocation letter', description_en = 'A letter of provisional allocation of rural concession in Mali is an act which grants the right to use land on a provisional basis, pending a definitive transfer of ownership after the development of the land. The process involves a formal request, verification of the conditions by the authorities, compliance with the clauses of the specifications and the possible obtaining of a land title (or a Final Concession Order - ACD) if the obligations are met. The processing time is not fixed and depends on several factors: nature and complexity of the file, verification of customary land rights, administrative coordination, field interventions, possible disputes and administrative workload. The applicant must anticipate a process which may be long and complex and whose exact duration is difficult to estimate in advance.', delai_en = 'Several months (deadline varies depending on complexity)' WHERE id = 33;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Urban concession for residential use (CUH)', titre_en = 'Obtain an Urban Concession for Housing Use (CUH)', description_en = 'The procedure for obtaining an Urban Concession for Housing Use (CUH) in Mali includes two main phases: obtaining a provisional title (the CUH) and its transformation into a definitive land title. Phase 1: Request for concession to state services, commodo and incommodo survey, demarcation and evaluation report, provisional concession order. Phase 2: Development within a specified time frame, application for land title, publication and registration. Processing times vary and depend on the speed of administrative services. The maximum time limit for obtaining a land title after development is 6 months.', delai_en = 'Duration varies depending on the speed of administrative services' WHERE id = 34;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Appeal of a court decision', titre_en = 'Appealing a judgment', description_en = 'To appeal a court decision in Mali, it is necessary to follow a rigorous procedure. The appeal allows the judgment to be reexamined by a higher court, usually the court of appeal. Conditions of appeal: Have the status of appellant (person dissatisfied with the decision), respect the deadlines (generally 10 days after the judgment is pronounced), take into account the formalities according to the procedural rules in force in Mali. The processing time by the court of appeal can vary considerably, as it depends on the workload of the court and the complexity of the case. It is strongly recommended to consult a specialized Malian lawyer to guide you in drafting documents, preparing arguments and monitoring deadlines.', delai_en = 'Appeal deadline: 10 days after the judgment is pronounced (or after notification in certain cases)' WHERE id = 36;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Authorization to sell property of a minor', titre_en = 'Obtain judicial authorization to sell the property of a minor', description_en = 'To sell the property of a minor, authorization is required due to their legal incapacity to carry out significant acts of disposition. The procedure to follow depends on the minor''s protection regime (legal administration or guardianship) and the type of property concerned. Under parental authority, the sale of real estate or other valuable property is strictly regulated by law and requires the approval of the guardianship judge. If the minor is placed under guardianship, the sale procedure is similar, but it is the family council which authorizes the sale, under the control of the judge. The money from the sale is placed in a blocked account in the name of the minor. It can only be used for its own benefit, and each use must be justified. If the sale is carried out without the necessary authorization, the act is void, and the minor may cancel it upon reaching the age of majority.', delai_en = 'Delays vary depending on the court''s workload and the complexity of the case' WHERE id = 37;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of a Simplified Single-Personal Stock Company (SASU)', titre_en = 'Create a Simplified Single-Personal Joint Stock Company (SASU) in Mali', description_en = 'In Mali, Single-Personal Simplified Joint Stock Companies (SASU) are governed by the law of the Organization for the Harmonization of Business Law in Africa (OHADA). The creation of a company is centralized through the Single Window of the Agency for the Promotion of Investments in Mali (API-Mali). The SASU offers great contractual freedom and does not require minimum capital, which facilitates its creation. The sole shareholder has liability limited to the amount of his contributions. The process includes drafting the statutes, depositing the share capital, obtaining supporting documents, submitting the file to the Single Window, registration and registration, and publication of the notice of incorporation.', delai_en = '72 hours after submission of the complete file' WHERE id = 42;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of a Single-Personal Limited Liability Company (SARL U)', titre_en = 'Create a Single-Personal Limited Liability Company (SARL U) in Mali', description_en = 'In Mali, the legal form of the single-member limited liability company is known as the Single-Personal Limited Liability Company (SARL U), in accordance with the law of the Organization for the Harmonization of Business Law in Africa (OHADA). SARL U is formed by a single person (natural or legal) with liability limited to the amount of their contributions. The minimum share capital required is one million CFA francs (1,000,000 FCFA), divided into equal shares with a minimum nominal value of 5,000 FCFA. Management is entrusted to a manager who may be the sole partner or a third party. The creation process is centralized by the API-Mali Single Window.', delai_en = '72 hours after submission of the complete file' WHERE id = 43;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Synthetic tax', titre_en = 'Subscribe to the synthetic tax regime', description_en = 'The synthetic tax is a simplified tax regime in Mali intended for small and medium-sized businesses. This regime allows taxpayers to benefit from a flat-rate tax based on objective criteria (turnover, number of employees, sector of activity) rather than on actual accounting. The synthetic tax applies to companies whose annual turnover does not exceed certain thresholds defined by the Directorate General of Taxes (DGI). This regime simplifies the accounting and tax obligations of small businesses while guaranteeing a fair contribution to tax.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the type of activity' WHERE id = 44;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on salaries and wages (I.T.S)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay tax on salaries and wages', description_en = 'The tax on salaries and wages (I.T.S) is applicable to all sums paid to employees by public and private employers, directly or through a third party, in return for or in connection with work. It applies to salaries, allowances, emoluments, commissions, participations, bonuses, gratuities, wages, tips and other remuneration. The tax is calculated according to a progressive scale and may be subject to reductions for family responsibilities. Declaration and payment are monthly.', delai_en = 'Monthly - before the 15th of the following month' WHERE id = 45;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'VAT declaration (Value Added Tax)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay Value Added Tax', description_en = 'Value Added Tax (VAT) is an indirect tax which applies to operations involving the sale of goods and the provision of services carried out in Mali by taxable persons. VAT is collected by taxable companies and remitted to the State. Businesses can deduct the VAT they paid on their purchases from the VAT they collect on their sales. Reporting and payment are monthly for most companies.', delai_en = 'Monthly - before the 15th of the following month' WHERE id = 46;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on industrial and commercial profits (IBIC/IS)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay income tax', description_en = 'The industrial and commercial profits tax (IBIC/IS) is a direct tax which applies to profits made by industrial and commercial companies in Mali. It concerns natural and legal persons carrying out an industrial, commercial or artisanal activity. The tax is calculated on the net profit made during the accounting year, after deduction of deductible expenses. The tax rate varies depending on the amount of profit and the status of the company (natural or legal person).', delai_en = 'Annual - before March 31 of the following year' WHERE id = 47;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Flat-rate contribution payable by employers (CFE)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay the CFE', description_en = 'The Flat-rate Contribution payable by Employers (CFE) is a direct tax that applies to public and private employers employing employees in Mali. It is calculated on the gross payroll paid to employees during the month. The CFE is intended to finance social benefits and collective facilities. The CFE rate is set by current regulations and may vary depending on the sector of activity and the size of the company.', delai_en = 'Monthly - before the 15th of the following month' WHERE id = 48;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'General Solidarity Contribution (CGS)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay the General Solidarity Contribution', description_en = 'The General Solidarity Contribution (CGS) is established by Law No. 2018-010 of February 12, 2018 for a period of three years for the benefit of the Sustainable Development Fund. It is based on the tax-free turnover generated by companies subject to the tax on industrial and commercial profits, corporate tax and synthetic tax. The CGS rate is set at 0.5%. The chargeable event and the chargeability are carried out under the same conditions as in matters of VAT. The declaration and payment follow the same deadlines and procedures as VAT.', delai_en = 'Monthly - before the 15th of the following month' WHERE id = 49;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Solidarity and Anti-Smoking Tax (TSLT)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay TSLT', description_en = 'The Solidarity and Smoking Control Tax (TSLT) is established by Law No. 2018-010 of February 12, 2018 for a period of three years for the benefit of the Sustainable Development Fund. It is due by manufacturers and importers of tobacco upon importation or upon delivery for consumption. The TSLT rate is set at 5%. The generating event is constituted by release for consumption for imported products and by the first delivery for consumption for products manufactured locally.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the type of operation' WHERE id = 50;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Professional patent and license', titre_en = 'Obtain the professional license and license', description_en = 'The professional license is a direct tax which applies to natural and legal persons carrying out a professional activity in Mali. It constitutes an annual tax payable by traders, manufacturers, craftsmen and service providers. The license is calculated according to a progressive scale based on the turnover or profits of the company. It also includes a license which authorizes the exercise of the activity. Payment of the license is obligatory for any person carrying out a professional activity subject to this tax.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the type of activity' WHERE id = 51;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Motor vehicle tax (Ordinary stickers)', titre_en = 'Obtain the automobile sticker', description_en = 'The motor vehicle tax, commonly known as a vignette, is an annual direct tax owed by motor vehicle owners in Mali. It applies to all motor vehicles registered in Mali, whether used for personal or professional purposes. The amount of the sticker varies depending on the tax power of the vehicle, its type (private, commercial, public transport) and its age. Payment of the sticker is obligatory and conditions the validity of the vehicle registration.', delai_en = 'Annual - before December 31' WHERE id = 52;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Property tax (T.F)', titre_en = 'Pay property tax', description_en = 'The property tax is an annual direct tax that applies to owners of real estate in Mali. It concerns all land, buildings and fixed installations located on Malian territory. The property tax is calculated on the cadastral rental value of real estate. It is due by the owner of the property on January 1 of the tax year. Payment of property tax is obligatory and conditions the peaceful enjoyment of the property.', delai_en = 'Annual - before December 31' WHERE id = 53;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Registration of a contract', titre_en = 'Register a contract', description_en = 'Registration of a contract is a mandatory formality for certain acts and contracts in Mali. This is a stamp duty which confers a certain date and enforceability to acts. Registration is mandatory for acts of sale, donation, sharing, lease, partnership, and other contracts according to the provisions of the General Tax Code. The registration fee is calculated according to a progressive or proportional scale depending on the type of document and its value.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on the type of contract' WHERE id = 54;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Agricultural profits tax (IBA)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay tax on agricultural profits', description_en = 'The agricultural profits tax (IBA) is a direct tax which applies to profits made by natural and legal persons carrying out agricultural activity in Mali. It concerns crop production, livestock, fishing, forestry and other related agricultural activities. The tax is calculated on the net profit made during the accounting year, after deduction of deductible expenses. The tax rate varies depending on the amount of profit and the status of the operator.', delai_en = 'Annual - before March 31 of the following year' WHERE id = 55;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Road Transport Tax (TTR)', titre_en = 'Pay road transport tax', description_en = 'The road transport tax (TTR) is a direct tax which applies to companies and individuals carrying out road transport activity in Mali. It concerns the transport of goods, passengers, and related transport services. The TTR is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of transport, the distance traveled, and the nature of the goods or passengers transported. Payment of the TTR is obligatory for any road transport activity subject to this tax.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on the type of transport' WHERE id = 56;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Special tax on certain products (ISCP)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay ISCP', description_en = 'The special tax on certain products (ISCP) is an indirect tax that applies to the production, import and sale of certain specific products in Mali. It concerns in particular luxury products, alcoholic beverages, tobacco products, and other products subject to special taxation. The ISCP is calculated according to a scale differentiated according to the type of product, its value, and its origin (local production or import). Payment of ISCP is mandatory for all products subject to this tax.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on the type of product' WHERE id = 57;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on financial activities (TAF)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay the TAF', description_en = 'The tax on financial activities (TAF) is an indirect tax that applies to financial operations and services in Mali. It concerns credit institutions, financial institutions, insurance companies, and other players in the financial sector. The TAF is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of financial transaction, its value, and the nature of the service provided. Payment of the TAF is obligatory for all financial transactions subject to this tax.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the type of activity' WHERE id = 58;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Land income declaration', titre_en = 'Declare land income', description_en = 'The property income declaration is a tax obligation that applies to property owners who receive rental income in Mali. It concerns all income derived from the rental of land, buildings, installations and other real estate. Property income is subject to income tax according to a progressive scale. The owner must declare his gross rental income, deduct deductible expenses, and calculate the net taxable income. This declaration is obligatory for any person receiving property income.', delai_en = 'Annual - before March 31 of the following year' WHERE id = 59;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Housing tax (TL)', titre_en = 'Pay housing tax', description_en = 'The housing tax (TL) is a direct tax that applies to owners and occupants of housing in Mali. It concerns all housing, whether occupied by its owners or rented to third parties. The housing tax is calculated according to a scale differentiated according to the type of accommodation, its surface area, its location, and its rental value. It is intended to finance collective facilities and urban services. Payment of housing tax is obligatory for all accommodation subject to this tax.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on the type of accommodation' WHERE id = 60;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on income from securities (IRVM)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay the IRVM', description_en = 'The securities income tax (IRVM) is a direct tax which applies to income derived from the holding and sale of securities in Mali. It concerns dividends, interest, capital gains on the sale of shares, bonds, shares, and other financial securities. The IRVM is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of income and the status of the taxpayer. Income from securities is subject to income tax according to the applicable rules. This declaration is mandatory for any person receiving income from securities.', delai_en = 'Annual - before March 31 of the following year' WHERE id = 61;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Property income tax (IRF)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay the IRF', description_en = 'The land income tax (IRF) is a direct tax that applies to income derived from the ownership and operation of real estate in Mali. It concerns rental income, subletting, transfer of usage rights, and other land income. The IRF is calculated according to a progressive scale on net taxable income after deduction of deductible expenses. Property income is subject to income tax according to the applicable rules. This declaration is obligatory for any person receiving property income.', delai_en = 'Annual - before March 31 of the following year' WHERE id = 62;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Patent on markets', titre_en = 'Pay the license on markets', description_en = 'The market license is a direct tax which applies to any person, resident or non-resident, who benefits from public procurement contracts in Mali. It concerns the delivery of goods and services to public or parapublic organizations. The market license is calculated on the amounts collected on the markets to which the company is awarded. This tax is intended to finance collective facilities and public services. Payment of the market license is obligatory for all beneficiaries of public procurement contracts.', delai_en = 'Annual - no later than January 30 of year N+1' WHERE id = 63;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tourist tax (T.T)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay tourist tax', description_en = 'The tourist tax (T.T) is an indirect tax that applies to tourist activities in Mali. It concerns hotel establishments, travel agencies, tourist guides, tourist restaurants, and other tourist service providers. The tourist tax is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of tourist activity and the turnover achieved. It is intended to finance the development of the tourism sector and tourist facilities. Payment of tourist tax is obligatory for all tourist service providers.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 64;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Internal tax on petroleum products (TIPP)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay the TIPP', description_en = 'The Internal Tax on Petroleum Products (TIPP) is an indirect tax that applies to petroleum products in Mali. It concerns the import, production, distribution and sale of petroleum products such as gasoline, diesel, kerosene, domestic fuel, etc. The TIPP is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of petroleum product and the quantities. It is intended to finance road infrastructure and community facilities. Payment of the TIPP is obligatory for all importers, producers and distributors of petroleum products.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 65;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Solidarity contribution on plane tickets (CSB)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay CSB', description_en = 'The Solidarity Contribution on plane tickets (CSB) is an indirect tax that applies to plane tickets issued in Mali. It concerns airlines, travel agencies, reservation platforms and all airline ticket issuers. The CSB is calculated according to a fixed or proportional scale on the amount of plane tickets issued. It is intended to finance solidarity and development actions. Payment of the CSB is mandatory for all airline ticket issuers.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 66;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on access to the telecommunications network (TARTOP)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay TARTOP', description_en = 'The Tax on access to the telecommunications network open to the public (TARTOP) is an indirect tax that applies to telecommunications operators in Mali. It concerns access to telecommunications networks open to the public, including mobile, landline, internet, and other telecommunications services. The TARTOP is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of service and the volume of traffic. It is intended to finance the development of telecommunications infrastructure and the regulation of the sector. Payment of TARTOP is mandatory for all telecommunications operators.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 67;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on insurance contracts (TCA)', titre_en = 'Declare and pay TCA', description_en = 'The Tax on Insurance Contracts (TCA) is an indirect tax that applies to insurance contracts in Mali. It concerns all types of insurance: car insurance, home insurance, life insurance, health insurance, business insurance, etc. The TCA is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of insurance and the amount of premiums. It is intended to finance the regulation of the insurance sector and collective facilities. Payment of TCA is mandatory for all insurers and insurance brokers.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 68;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Tax on gold exporters not governed by the mining code', titre_en = 'Declare and pay tax on gold', description_en = 'The Tax on gold exporters not governed by the mining code is an indirect tax that applies to gold exporters in Mali who are not subject to the mining code regime. It concerns artisanal gold exporters, gold traders, and other players in the gold sector not covered by the mining code. The tax is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the type of export and the quantity of gold exported. It is intended to finance the development of the artisanal mining sector and the regulation of the gold industry. Payment of this tax is obligatory for all gold exporters not governed by the mining code.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 69;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'The samples', titre_en = 'Make mandatory withdrawals', description_en = 'Withholdings are withholding taxes made by employers, clients, or paying organizations on income, salaries, fees, and other amounts paid. They concern in particular deductions from salaries (withholding tax), deductions from fees, deductions from property income, deductions from commercial profits, etc. The levies are calculated according to specific scales and are paid to the tax administration. They constitute a mechanism for early tax recovery. Compliance with direct debit obligations is mandatory for all paying agencies.', delai_en = 'Variable depending on the type of collection' WHERE id = 70;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Regulatory fees and recovery on public markets', titre_en = 'Pay the regulatory fee', description_en = 'The Regulatory Fee and Recovery on Public Procurement is a direct tax that applies to beneficiaries of public procurement in Mali. It concerns all types of public contracts: supplies, services, works, and other services. The regulation fee is calculated according to a differentiated scale depending on the amount of the contract and the type of service. It is intended to finance the regulation and control of public markets, as well as the development of collective facilities. Payment of this fee is obligatory for all beneficiaries of public contracts.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on the type of market' WHERE id = 71;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Gun tax', titre_en = 'Report and pay gun tax', description_en = 'The Firearms Tax is an indirect tax that applies to firearms in Mali. It concerns the importation, sale, possession, and use of firearms by individuals, security companies, law enforcement, and other authorized holders. The tax is calculated according to a scale differentiated according to the type of weapon, its caliber, and its use. It is intended to finance the regulation and control of firearms, as well as public safety. Payment of this tax is obligatory for all firearm owners.', delai_en = 'Monthly - in the first half of the following month' WHERE id = 72;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Theft declaration', titre_en = 'Report a theft to the authorities', description_en = 'Reporting theft in Mali is made to a police station or gendarmerie brigade. This procedure makes it possible to officially record the theft in a register and obtain a certificate of loss or theft necessary for administrative or insurance procedures. The report must be made as quickly as possible after discovery of the theft to facilitate the investigation. For official documents such as a passport, the declaration can also be made to the prefect. Criminal procedures relating to theft are governed by the Malian Code of Criminal Procedure.', delai_en = 'Immediately after discovery of the theft' WHERE id = 75;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Creation of a Company in Collective Name (SNC)', titre_en = 'Create an SNC', description_en = 'The Collective Company (SNC) is a legal form of business regulated by the OHADA Uniform Act relating to commercial company law. It is characterized by strong mutual trust between partners who all have the status of merchants and joint and indefinite liability. At least two partners are required, with no minimum share capital. The partners are liable for the debts indefinitely and jointly. The creation takes place at the API-Mali Single Window which centralizes all administrative formalities. This form is particularly suitable for small family businesses where trust between partners is strong.', delai_en = '72 hours after validation of the file' WHERE id = 76;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Allocation of social housing', titre_en = 'Obtain social housing', description_en = NULL, delai_en = 'Varies depending on availability and review of files' WHERE id = 77;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Lease request', titre_en = 'Obtain a rental lease', description_en = NULL, delai_en = 'Variable depending on the diligence of the parties and the obtaining of documents' WHERE id = 78;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Individual Descriptive Sheet (IDF) NINA', titre_en = 'Obtain your NINA individual file', description_en = 'The NINA Individual Descriptive Sheet (FDI) in Mali is an official document that can be obtained via a dematerialized tele-request platform. This procedure includes enrolling in the Civil Status Administrative Census (RAVEC) to obtain a NINA number, then requesting the individual file via the platform www.citede.ml or by email to fidi@ctdec.ml. The process is largely dematerialized and free. For Malians living abroad, consulates also offer application forms. This procedure is governed by Law No. 06-040 of August 11, 2006 establishing the National Identification Number (NINA) in Mali.

Main center: National Directorate of Civil Status (DNEC)
Address: Route de Kati, Bamako
Website: dnec.gouv.ml
Function: Manages the national file and processes complex requests.', delai_en = 'Varies depending on request method' WHERE id = 80;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Certificate of residence', titre_en = 'Obtain a residence certificate', description_en = 'The certificate of residence in Mali is a simple and quick administrative document to obtain for Malian citizens. This procedure consists of going to the police station or town hall of your place of residence with the required documents, filling out a form, answering the officer''s questions about the length of residence, and paying the tax stamp. The document is issued free of charge, only the tax stamp costs 200 CFA francs. For foreigners, specific procedures exist for obtaining an ordinary resident card valid for three years. This procedure is governed by Law 04-058 of November 25, 2004 and Decree 05-322 of February 11, 2009.', delai_en = 'Less than 24 hours' WHERE id = 82;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Change your car into a taxi', titre_en = 'Transform your personal car into a taxi', description_en = 'Transforming a personal car into a taxi in Mali involves a complex administrative process which requires changing the use of the vehicle and obtaining several documents specific to public transport. This procedure includes checking the prerequisites, passing the technical inspection, obtaining the transport license, taking out specific insurance, and administrative procedures for the vehicle and the driver. The process involves several entities: National Transport Directorate, Bamako District Town Hall, and National Road Safety Agency (ANASER). This procedure is governed by the laws and decrees on road transport of the Ministry of Transport and Infrastructure.

Centers involved:
- Directorate General of Taxes (for taxes)
- Ministry of Equipment and Transport (authorization)
- Regional Directorate of Land and Water Transport (DRTTF) (registration)', delai_en = 'Several weeks for all the procedures' WHERE id = 83;
UPDATE procedures SET nom_en = 'Eassay_gently', titre_en = 'Temporary_test', description_en = '1 to 1 CV', delai_en = '1 day' WHERE id = 84;

